        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 4:08PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Divide, or 17 miles northwest of Colorado Springs, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colorado Springs, Woodland Park, Air Force Academy, Manitou Springs,
Green Mountain Falls, Divide, Stratmoor, Crystola, Chipita Park,
Cascade, and Fort Carson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 PM MDT for
central and east central Colorado.</instruction>
